 Bitwise Operator ->
            Bitwise operators work at the binary lavel(bits).
            Every number inside a computer is stored in binary(0s and 1s).
            Exa -> 5 -> 00000101 -> sabse right wale bit (1) ko "least significant bit" kahte hai
                                    aur sabse left wale bit (0) ko "most significant bit" kahte hai
                   3 -> 00000011
            Bitwise operators perform operations bit by bit.

 Why Learn Bitwise Operators? ->
      Bitwise operators are used in:
            optimizing code
            competitive programming
            system-level programming
            cryptography
            fast calculations
            DSA tricks (very important for interviews)
            performance-critical logic
            state compression problems
            advanced algorithms

 Types of Bitwise Operators ->
    & -> AND
    | -> OR
    ^ -> XOR
    ~ -> NOT
    << -> LeftShift
    >> -> RightShift
    >>> -> Unsigned Right Shift
